I"<p>This is a test of the blog of Tyler Jackson. This is only a test.</p>

<p>The motivation for this blog is to learn in public, most recently coming from <a href="https://www.joshwcomeau.com/blog/how-to-learn-stuff-quickly">Josh Comeau’s <em>How to Learn Stuff Quickly</em></a>.</p>

<p>I set this blog up by kinda sorta following <a href="https://jvns.ca/blog/2014/10/08/how-to-set-up-a-blog-in-5-minutes/">Julia Evans’s <em>How to set up a blog in 5 minutes</em></a>. Though it certainly took more than 5 minutes. Additional steps that I took are a follows:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Install ruby 3.0.0 via:</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"><span class="nv">$ </span>brew <span class="nb">install </span>ruby</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>Install rbenv via:</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"><span class="nv">$ </span>brew <span class="nb">install </span>rbenv</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>Add</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="n">gem</span> <span class="s2">"webrick"</span></code></pre></figure>
<p>to the Gemfile because <a href="https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/issues/8523">webrick is no longer a standard library</a>.</p>
